n to publish seminal texts on the cubist paintings of Georges Braque and Pablo Picasso. His contributions to the surrealist magazine Documents (which Einstein cofounded with Georges Bataille), including writings on Picasso and Paul Klee, remain unsurpassed in their depth and complexity.In a series of close visual analyses—illustrated with major works by Braque, Picasso, and Klee—Zeidler retrieves the theoretical resources that Einstein brought to bear on their art. Form as Revolt shows us that to rediscover Einstein's art criticism is to see the work of great modernist artists anew through the eyes of one of the most gifted left-wing formalists of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aArt History. 4aJewish Studies. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2016z9783110485165oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170190040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501701900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501701900/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DPKb2016